  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you take a screenshot on a Mac?",
  "response": "Taking a screenshot on a Mac is simple and can be done using keyboard shortcuts. Here are the common methods:\n\n### 1. **Capture the Entire Screen:**\n   - Press **Command (\u2318) + Shift + 3**.\n   - The screenshot will be saved as a file on your desktop by default.\n\n### 2. **Capture a Selected Portion of the Screen:**\n   - Press **Command (\u2318) + Shift + 4**.\n   - Your pointer will turn into a crosshair. Click and drag to select the area you want to capture.\n   - Release the mouse button or trackpad to take the screenshot. It will be saved on your desktop.\n\n### 3. **Capture a Specific Window:**\n   - Press **Command (\u2318) + Shift + 4**, then press the **Spacebar**.\n   - The pointer will change to a camera icon. Move the camera over the window you want to capture.\n   - Click to take the screenshot. It will be saved on your desktop.\n\n### 4. **Take a Screenshot and Copy to Clipboard (Not Save):**\n   - Add **Control** to any of the above shortcuts:\n     - **Command (\u2318) + Control + Shift + 3**: Full screen to clipboard.\n     - **Command (\u2318) + Control + Shift + 4**: Selected portion to clipboard.\n     - **Command (\u2318) + Control + Shift + 4**, then **Spacebar**: Specific window to clipboard.\n   - The screenshot will be copied to your clipboard and can be pasted (e.g., into a document or image editor) instead of being saved to the desktop.\n\n### 5. **Using the Screenshot Tool (macOS Mojave and Later):**\n   - Press **Command (\u2318) + Shift + 5** to open the Screenshot toolbar.\n   - Choose to capture the entire screen, a selected portion, or a specific window. You can also record your screen.\n   - Click **Capture** to take the screenshot.\n\n### Where to Find Screenshots:\nBy default, screenshots are saved as `.png` files on your desktop. You can change the save location or format in the Screenshot toolbar options (accessible via **Command (\u2318) + Shift + 5**).\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
